Levinas’ calculations on who and how much is entitled to our attention bring us back to this socio-political situation about the division of the relational sphere and its influence on the opportunities available to women, which, in turn, may set forth their freedom, and lead them to compose new relations among people.
We can perceive such a divide between mine and your by studying how people’s daily routine oscillates between what is immediately outside of their sphere—tasks involving other people—and what is within their sphere, routine tasks they need to perform to meet their own needs. The prior responsibility for children’s essential nutrients is assigned to the woman on account of her being the one spending the most time with them; but, within a desiring relationship, it is no longer appointed
nor prefigured; it arises due to her not succeeding in performing the same task as well as her partner.
The free choice of Chilean couples to assemble due to a meaningful bond where the partners need each other does not mean having the capacity to conceive a family created on the basis of intersubjectivity and responsibility of itself; but instead, it occurs as a question whose solution is uncertain, as we have been saying.
